			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The level 30 wont get xp grouped with you.  HIghest level person you can group with is 50% more than your level rounded up * i think *.  Or you can view it as lowest level person you can group with is 2/3 your level.  So 45 for instance could group with 30.
<br />

<br />
At the low ended levels the pets do some really nice damage in comparison with most classes and would be pretty strong.  The beastlord pet in my experience with a high aggro proc on, and the other pet having taunt off, they can pretty much keep aggro on just about anything pet wise.  I am not sure about comparing it to the stunning mage pet however.
<br />

<br />
I wouldnt really look at the earth pets root as much of an advantage since the pet toys and procs tend to shred root off in a millesecond.  This always seems to happen at the worst possible moments as well.
<br />

<br />
As for the combo....there is worse out there, there is better.  NOthing is wrong with it.  The mage wont be able to bind wounds for a lot since i believe theirs caps at 100?
<br />

<br />
If I was to run two accounts on the same box I would probably go with a cleric however.  Get them a horse and just tap over every now and then to CH.  I like meleeing a lot better than pet healing, so this would be preferable in my opinion.  I just have the feeling the amount of juggling involved with a mage/bst would be far too much.  If you are up to it however *shrug*...why not..</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
