			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I play a split screen BST/MAG duo and the combo works very well.  Since there is no real healer, you'll have to sit out a few to heal/med up, but just using pets/nukes/dots works really well.  I think the first thing to keep in mind is which pet do you want to tank.  Beastlords can far outheal their pets over mages, so at comperable levels it would be hard to pass up BST pet tanking (even though the mage earth pet has slightly higher base HP 4800hp vs. 4500hp).  In that case I believe water pet does the most damage as long as pet is backstabbing (which mob positioning can be a pain at times with pet tanking).  
<br />

<br />
If you want the Mage to tank, I would recommend the air pet over the earth pet even though the difference in HP is fairly large.  The root effect from the earth pet makes things goofy if you are split screening since whichever pet is closest to mob when rooted gets agro.  It's not that big of a deal, just you'll end up healing 2 pets instead of one.  Air pet has slightly less HP, but still tanks well cause of the stun effect and high agility.  For standard exping, air pet is more than adequate IMO.  Keep in mind i'm talking about playing 2 toons on same computer and the last thing you want to do is have to keep on alt-tabbing back and forth to keep both pets alive <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />.<br />_________________<br />Grexx
<br />
54 Primalist 
<br />
Maelin Starpyre</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
