			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Fire and water pets both have damaging procs, while Fire gets a DS, water gets backstab.  The DS on a fire pet only helps if it is tanking, while the mage can position his pet to backstab.  Although the fire ds is greater than a mages spell, the lack of hps a fire pet has isn't worth the extra few pts for a ds that it will never use as it isn't tanking
<br />

<br />
In general, a bst's pet will out aggro a mage pet w/ ease.  The procs bst get genearate great aggo.  I've been in DPS groups (aka 4 mage, bst, cleric) and my pet easily gets aggro over any of the mage pets.
<br />

<br />
Stuns are good as in the 50's your mage pets will have weapons that proc, so giving up the damage on thier innate proc really isnt too big a deal.  Stuns allow you and your pet (if it tanks) to take less damage, resulting in less heals, and less down time.<br />_________________<br /><FONT color=#cc0000>Elder Shenk Windu 66 Savage Lord</FONT><FONT color=#0000ff><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1103958">Shenk</A></A></FONT></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
