			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Khauruk wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I've been reading mage forums, and they seem to have little use for fire pets once you get into the 50s.  Have any duo-ers found this to be the same?  Does the wizard pet do decent enough spell damage to make up for the lack of melee, or are the air pets stuns &gt; most for meleeing beasts?  I'm asking since I don't want the mage pet getting agro if possible.  Also, how do you find the monster summoning spells for duoing?  Can you tell which type of pet you're getting (for non-fire pets)?  Is the damage greater than the standard melee pets?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Fire pets after 49th level are piss poor wizards.  They have a miniscule mana pool, which they mostly waste buffing.  After they burn through their mana pool, they resort to weak melee.  They don't have DS, they don't have a fire proc.  They suck at tanking.
<br />

<br />
I think I've pulled out my 50+ fire pet perhaps a dozen times in 4 years of play... and each and every time I'm reconvinced they're crap.
<br />

<br />
Now.... get a level 3 or 4 focus item, and their spell selection changes quite a bit so they're a bit more useful.  However, add it all together and they're still not as good as an air pet or water pet for dps.  Especially if the air/water pet is focused as well.
<br />

<br />
To answer the original question... I duoed with a beastlord for over a year during our 50's and low 60's.  It was an awesome combo... the only thing we were lacking were ports and snare.  Air pets combined with Rellic work really well for runners ... you can't run when you're stun locked.  Mages also can relieve that mob of their last 20% of hps fairly quickly.  If you're going for pure dps, then position things so that the water pet has backstab and you're good to go.  Beastlord slows allow the mage to keep up with healing their own pets as needed, mages have summoned items, and beastlord buffs are perfect for pets.
<br />

<br />
Very solid duo.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=502692&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Zashir Swiftpaw</span></a> -- Beastlord
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=171313&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Eloina Pyromancer</span></a> -- Arch Mage
<br />
Torvonnilous</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
